               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-634" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-634" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-634" type="surname" value="JONES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400406-name-634" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS JONES</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to Henry Adams Newman, a slop-seller, in High-street, Shadwell. On the 14th of March I missed a pair of corduroy trowsers from the door-post—I had seen them safe ten minutes before—I ran up the highway, and saw the prisoner running with them under his arm—I stopped him, and asked where he got them—he said he picked them up—here is the shop-ticket on them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400406-name-635" type="witnessName">
